Preheat your #grill{} to high.

Sprinkle the @za'atar{1%tsp} spice over the @British chicken breasts{2} and grate on
the zest of the @lemon{1/2}.

Season with @salt{} and drizzle on a splash of @oil{1%splash}. Rub the flavours
into the chicken and pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken.

Pop the baking tray under the grill. Grill the chicken until cooked through and
golden, ~{15-18%minutes}, turning halfway.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is done when no longer pink in the middle!

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and
all). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%cup}. Trim the @courgette{1}, quarter lengthways
then chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the courgette,
garlic and @ground cumin{2%tsp}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}, then add the
@water{75%ml}.

Bring to the boil then stir in the @KNORR chicken stock{1/2} and lentils. Simmer
until the courgette is tender, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

When the chicken is ready, transfer to a #plate{}. Squeeze over some lemon juice
and sprinkle over half the parsley. Keep to one side.

Stir the @creme fraiche{112.5%g} into the lentils and bring to the boil. Stir in
the remaining parsley and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the lentils between your #bowls{} and top with the chicken. Enjoy!